\v 1 \w  [“] Hear  |strong="8085" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.1" \w* \w  this ,  |strong="2063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.2" \w* \w  O priests !  |strong="3548" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.3" \w* \w  Take heed ,  |strong="7181" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.4" \w* \w  O house  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.5" \w* \w  of Israel !  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.6" \w* \w  Give ear ,  |strong="238" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.9" \w* \w  O royal  |strong="4428" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.8" \w* \w  house !  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.7" \w* \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.10" \w* \w  this judgment  |strong="4941" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.12" \w* \w  is against you  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.11" \w* \w  because  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.13" \w* \w  you have been  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.15" \w* \w  a snare  |strong="6341" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.14" \w* \w  at Mizpah ,  |strong="4709" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.16" \w* \w  a net  |strong="7568" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.17" \w* \w  spread out  |strong="6566" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.18" \w* \w  on  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.19" \w* \w  Tabor .  |strong="8396" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.1.20" \w* \v 2 \w  The rebels  |strong="7846" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.2" \w* \w  are deep  |strong="6009" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.3" \w* \w  in slaughter ;  |strong="7819" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.1" \w* \w  but I  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.4" \w* \w  will chastise them  |strong="4148" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.5" \w* \w  all .  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.2.6" \w* \v 3 \w  I  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.1" \w* \w  know all about  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.2" \w* \w  Ephraim ,  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.3" \w* \f + \fr 5.3 \ft That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verses 5, 9, 11, 12, 13, and 14 \f* \w  and Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.4" \w* \w  is not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.5" \w* \w  hidden  |strong="3582" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.6" \w* \w  from Me .  |strong="4480" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.7" \w* \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.8" \w* \w  now ,  |strong="6258" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.9" \w* \w  O Ephraim ,  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.11" \w* \w  you have turned to prostitution ;  |strong="2181" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.10" \w* \w  Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.13" \w* \w  is defiled .  |strong="2930" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.3.12" \w* \v 4 \w  Their deeds  |strong="4611" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.3" \w* \w  do not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.1" \w* \w  permit them  |strong="5414" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.2" \w* \w  to return  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.4" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.5" \w* \w  their God ,  |strong="430" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.6" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.7" \w* \w  a spirit  |strong="7307" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.8" \w* \w  of prostitution  |strong="2183" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.9" \w* \w  is within them ,  |strong="7130" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.10" \w* \w  and they do not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.13" \w* \w  know  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.14" \w* \w  the LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.4.12" \w* \v 5 \w  Israel’s  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.3" \w* \w  arrogance  |strong="1347" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.2" \w* \w  testifies  |strong="6030" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.1" \w* \w  against them ;  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.4" \w* \w  Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.5" \w* \w  and Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.6" \w* \w  stumble  |strong="3782" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.7" \w* \w  in their iniquity ;  |strong="5771" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.8" \w* \w  even  |strong="1571" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.10" \w* \w  Judah  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.11" \w* \w  stumbles  |strong="3782" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.9" \w* \w  with them .  |strong="5973" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.5.12" \w* \v 6 \w  They go  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.3" \w* \w  with their flocks  |strong="6629" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.1" \w* \w  and herds  |strong="1241" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.2" \w* \w  to seek  |strong="1245" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.4" \w* \w  the LORD ,  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.6" \w* \w  but they do not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.7" \w* \w  find Him ;  |strong="4672" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.8" \w* \w  He has withdrawn Himself  |strong="2502" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.9" \w* \w  from them .  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.6.10" \w* \v 7 \w  They have been unfaithful  |strong="898" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.2" \w* \w  to the LORD ;  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.1" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.3" \w* \w  they have borne  |strong="3205" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.6" \w* \w  illegitimate  |strong="2114" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.5" \w* \w  children .  |strong="1121" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.4" \w* \w  Now  |strong="6258" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.7" \w* \w  the New Moon  |strong="2320" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.9" \w* \f + \fr 5.7 \ft Or "their New Moon feast" or "the coming month" \f* \w  . . .  |strong="854" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.10" \w* \w  will devour them  |strong="398" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.8" \w* \w  along with their land .  |strong="2506" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.7.11" \w* \v 8 \w  Blow  |strong="8628" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.1" \w* \w  the ram’s horn  |strong="7782" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.2" \w* \w  in Gibeah ,  |strong="1390" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.3" \w* \w  the trumpet  |strong="2689" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.4" \w* \w  in Ramah ;  |strong="7414" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.5" \w* \w  raise the battle cry  |strong="7321" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.6" \w* \w  vvv  |strong="1007" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.7" \w* \w  in Beth-aven :  |strong="1007" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.8" \w* \f + \fr 5.8 \ft "Beth-aven" means "house of wickedness". This is a derogatory term for Bethel, which means "house of God"; see 1 Kings 12:28–29. \f* \w  Lead on ,  |strong="310" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.9" \w* \w  O Benjamin !  |strong="1144" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.8.10" \w* \v 9 \w  Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.1" \w* \w  will be  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.3" \w* \w  laid waste  |strong="8047" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.2" \w* \w  on the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.4" \w* \w  of rebuke .  |strong="8433" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.5" \w* \w  Among the tribes  |strong="7626" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.6" \w* \w  of Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.7" \w* \w  I proclaim  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.8" \w* \w  what is certain .  |strong="539" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.9.9" \w* \v 10 \w  The princes  |strong="8269" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.2" \w* \w  of Judah  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.3" \w* \w  are like those  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.1" \w* \w  who move  |strong="5253" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.4" \w* \w  boundary stones ;  |strong="1366" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.5" \w* \f + \fr 5.10 \ft See Proverbs 22:28 and Proverbs 23:10. \f* \w  I will pour out  |strong="8210" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.7" \w* \w  My fury  |strong="5678" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.9" \w* \w  upon them  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.6" \w* \w  like water .  |strong="4325" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.10.8" \w* \v 11 \w  Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.2" \w* \w  is oppressed ,  |strong="6231" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.1" \w* \w  crushed  |strong="7533" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.3" \w* \w  in judgment ,  |strong="4941" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.4" \w* \w  for  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.5" \w* \w  he is determined  |strong="2974" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.6" \w* \w  to follow  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.7" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="310" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.8" \w* \w  worthless idols .  |strong="6673" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.11.9" \w* \f + \fr 5.11 \ft Or "to follow human precepts" \f* \v 12 \w  So I am  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.1" \w* \w  like a moth  |strong="6211" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.2" \w* \w  to Ephraim ,  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.3" \w* \w  and like decay  |strong="7538" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.4" \w* \w  to the house  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.5" \w* \w  of Judah .  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.12.6" \w* \v 13 \w  When Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.2" \w* \w  saw  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.1" \w* \w  his sickness  |strong="2483" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.4" \w* \w  and Judah  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.5" \w* \w  his wound ,  |strong="4205" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.7" \w* \w  then Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.9" \w* \w  turned  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.8" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.10" \w* \w  Assyria  |strong="804" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.11" \w* \w  and sent  |strong="7971" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.12" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.13" \w* \w  the great  |strong="3377" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.15" \w* \w  king .  |strong="4428" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.14" \w* \f + \fr 5.13 \ft Or "to King Jareb" \f* \w  But he  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.16" \w* \w  cannot  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.17" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3201" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.18" \w* \w  cure  |strong="7495" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.19" \w* \w  you  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.20" \w* \w  [or]  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.21" \w* \w  heal  |strong="1455" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.22" \w* \w  . . .  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.23" \w* \w  your wound .  |strong="4205" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.13.24" \w* \v 14 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.1" \w* \w  I  |strong="595" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.2" \w* \w  am like a lion  |strong="7826" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.3" \w* \w  to Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.4" \w* \w  and like a young lion  |strong="3715" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.5" \w* \w  to the house  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.6" \w* \w  of Judah .  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.7" \w* \w  I ,  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.8" \w* \w  [even] I ,  |strong="589" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.9" \w* \w  will tear them to pieces  |strong="2963" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.10" \w* \w  and then go away .  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.11" \w* \w  I will carry them off  |strong="5375" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.12" \w* \w  [where] no one  |strong="369" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.13" \w* \w  can rescue them .  |strong="5337" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.14.14" \w* \v 15 \w  Then I will return  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.1" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.2" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.3" \w* \w  My place  |strong="4725" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.4" \w* \w  until  |strong="5704" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.5" \w* \w  they admit their guilt  |strong="816" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.7" \w* \w  and seek  |strong="1245" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.8" \w* \w  My face ;  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.9" \w* \w  in their affliction  |strong="6862" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.10" \w* \w  they will earnestly seek Me  |strong="7836" srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.12" \w* \w  . . . . ”  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.5.15.11" \w* 
\c 6
\p

\s The Unrepentance of Israel and Judah
\p
\v 1 \w  Come ,  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.1" \w* \w  let us return  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.2" \w* \w  to  |strong="413" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.3" \w* \w  the LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.4" \w* \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.5" \w* \w  He  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.6" \w* \w  has torn us to pieces ,  |strong="2963" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.7" \w* \w  but He will heal us ;  |strong="7495" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.8" \w* \w  He has wounded us ,  |strong="5221" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.9" \w* \w  but He will bind up our wounds .  |strong="2280" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.1.10" \w* \v 2 \w  After two days  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.2" \w* \w  He will revive us ;  |strong="2421" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.1" \w* \w  on the third  |strong="7992" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.4" \w* \w  day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.3" \w* \w  He will raise us up ,  |strong="6965" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.5" \w* \w  that we may live  |strong="2421" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.6" \w* \w  in His presence .  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.2.7" \w* \v 3 \w  So let us know —  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.1" \w* \w  let us press on  |strong="7291" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.2" \w* \w  to know  |strong="3045" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.3" \w* \w   |strong="853" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.4" \w* \w  the LORD .  |strong="3068" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.5" \w* \w  As surely as  |strong="3559" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.7" \w* \w  the sun rises ,  |strong="7837" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.6" \w* \w  He will appear ;  |strong="4161" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.8" \w* \w  He will come  |strong="935" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.9" \w* \w  to us  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.11" \w* \w  like the rain ,  |strong="1653" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.10" \w* \w  like the spring showers  |strong="4456" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.12" \w* \w  that water  |strong="3384" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.13" \w* \w  the earth .  |strong="776" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.3.14" \w* \v 4 \w  What  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.1" \w* \w  shall I do  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.2" \w* \w  with you ,  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.3" \w* \w  O Ephraim ?  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.4" \w* \f + \fr 6.4 \ft That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verse 10 \f* \w  What  |strong="4100" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.5" \w* \w  shall I do  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.6" \w* \w  with you ,  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.7" \w* \w  O Judah ?  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.8" \w* \w  For your loyalty  |strong="2617" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.9" \w* \w  is like a morning  |strong="1242" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.11" \w* \w  mist ,  |strong="6051" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.10" \w* \w  like the early  |strong="7925" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.13" \w* \w  dew  |strong="2919" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.12" \w* \w  that vanishes .  |strong="1980" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.4.14" \w* \v 5 \w  Therefore  |strong="5921" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.1" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3651" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.2" \w* \w  I have hewn [them]  |strong="2672" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.3" \w* \w  by the prophets ;  |strong="5030" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.4" \w* \w  I have slain them  |strong="2026" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.5" \w* \w  by the words  |strong="561" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.6" \w* \w  of My mouth ,  |strong="6310" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.7" \w* \w  and My judgments  |strong="4941" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.8" \w* \w  go forth  |strong="3318" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.10" \w* \w  like lightning .  |strong="216" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.5.9" \w* \v 6 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.1" \w* \w  I desire  |strong="2654" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.3" \w* \w  mercy ,  |strong="2617" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.2" \w* \w  not  |strong="3808" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.4" \w* \w  sacrifice ,  |strong="2077" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.5" \w* \f + \fr 6.6 \ft Cited in Matthew 9:13 and Matthew 12:7 \f* \w  and the knowledge  |strong="1847" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.6" \w* \w  of God  |strong="430" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.7" \w* \w  rather than burnt offerings .  |strong="5930" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.6.8" \w* \v 7 \w  But they ,  |strong="1992" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.1" \w* \w  like Adam ,  |strong="121" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.2" \w* \w  have transgressed  |strong="5674" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.3" \w* \f + \fr 6.7 \ft Or "As at Adam, they have transgressed" \f* \w  the covenant ;  |strong="1285" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.4" \w* \w  there  |strong="8033" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.5" \w* \w  they were unfaithful  |strong="898" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.6" \w* \w  to Me .  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.7.7" \w* \v 8 \w  Gilead  |strong="1568" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.1" \w* \w  is a city  |strong="7151" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.2" \w* \w  of evildoers  |strong="6466" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.3" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="205" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.4" \w* \w  tracked with footprints  |strong="6121" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.5" \w* \w  of blood .  |strong="1818" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.8.6" \w* \v 9 \w  Like raiders  |strong="1416" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.3" \w* \w  who lie in ambush  |strong="2442" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.1" \w* \w  . . . ,  |strong="376" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.2" \w* \w  [so does] a band  |strong="2267" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.4" \w* \w  of priests ;  |strong="3548" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.5" \w* \w  they murder  |strong="7523" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.7" \w* \w  on the way  |strong="1870" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.6" \w* \w  to Shechem ;  |strong="7927" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.8" \w* \w  surely  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.9" \w* \w  they have committed  |strong="6213" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.11" \w* \w  atrocities .  |strong="2154" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.9.10" \w* \v 10 \w  In the house  |strong="1004" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.1" \w* \w  of Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.2" \w* \w  I have seen  |strong="7200" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.3" \w* \w  a horrible thing :  |strong="8186" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.4" \w* \w  Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.7" \w* \w  practices prostitution  |strong="2184" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.6" \w* \w  there ,  |strong="8033" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.5" \w* \w  [and] Israel  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.9" \w* \w  is defiled .  |strong="2930" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.10.8" \w* \v 11 \w  Also  |strong="1571" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.1" \w* \w  for you ,  |srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.5" \w* \w  O Judah ,  |strong="3063" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.2" \w* \w  a harvest  |strong="7105" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.4" \w* \w  is appointed ,  |strong="7896" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.3" \w* \w  when I restore  |strong="7725" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.6" \w* \w  My people  |strong="5971" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.8" \w* \w  from captivity .  |strong="7622" srcloc="WLC:HOS.6.11.7" \w* \f + \fr 6.11 \ft Or "restore the fortunes of My people" \f* 
