\s Ephraim’s Iniquity
\p
\v 1 \w  When I heal  |strong="7495" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.1" \w* \w  Israel ,  |strong="3478" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.2" \w* \w  the iniquity  |strong="5771" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.4" \w* \w  of Ephraim  |strong="669" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.5" \w* \f + \fr 7.1 \ft That is, the northern kingdom of Israel; also in verses 8 and 11 \f* \w  will be exposed ,  |strong="1540" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.3" \w* \w  as well as the crimes  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.6" \w* \w  of Samaria .  |strong="8111" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.7" \w* \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.8" \w* \w  they practice  |strong="6466" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.9" \w* \w  deceit  |strong="8267" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.10" \w* \w  and thieves  |strong="1590" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.11" \w* \w  break in ;  |strong="935" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.12" \w* \w  bandits  |strong="1416" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.14" \w* \w  raid  |strong="6584" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.13" \w* \w  in the streets .  |strong="2351" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.1.15" \w* \v 2 \w  But they fail to  |strong="1077" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.1" \w* \w  consider  |strong="559" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.2" \w* \w  in their hearts  |strong="3824" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.3" \w* \w  that I remember  |strong="2142" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.6" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.4" \w* \w  their evil .  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.5" \w* \w  Now  |strong="6258" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.7" \w* \w  their deeds  |strong="4611" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.9" \w* \w  are all around them ;  |strong="5437" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.8" \w* \w  they are  |strong="1961" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.12" \w* \w  before  |strong="5048" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.10" \w* \w  My face .  |strong="6440" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.2.11" \w* \v 3 \w  They delight  |strong="8055" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.3.2" \w* \w  the king  |strong="4428" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.3.3" \w* \w  with their evil ,  |strong="7451" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.3.1" \w* \w  and the princes  |strong="8269" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.3.5" \w* \w  with their lies .  |strong="3585" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.3.4" \w* \v 4 \w  They are all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.1" \w* \w  adulterers ,  |strong="5003" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.2" \w* \w  like  |strong="3644" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.3" \w* \w  an oven  |strong="8574" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.4" \w* \w  heated  |strong="1197" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.5" \w* \w  by a baker  |strong="644" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.6" \w* \w  who needs not  |strong="7673" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.7" \w* \w  stoke the fire  |strong="5782" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.8" \w* \w  from the kneading  |strong="3888" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.9" \w* \w  to  |strong="5704" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.11" \w* \w  the rising  |strong="2556" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.12" \w* \w  of the dough .  |strong="1217" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.4.10" \w* \v 5 \w  The princes  |strong="8269" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.4" \w* \w  are inflamed  |strong="2470" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.3" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="2534" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.5" \w* \w  with wine  |strong="3196" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.6" \w* \w  on the day  |strong="3117" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.1" \w* \w  of our king ;  |strong="4428" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.2" \w* \w  so he joins hands  |strong="4900" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.7" \w* \w  . . .  |strong="3027" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.8" \w* \w  with  |strong="854" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.9" \w* \w  those who mock him .  |strong="3887" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.5.10" \w* \v 6 \w  For  |strong="3588" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.1" \w* \w  they prepare  |strong="7126" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.2" \w* \w  their heart  |strong="3820" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.4" \w* \w  like an oven  |strong="8574" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.3" \w* \w  while they lie in wait ;  |strong="696" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.5" \w* \w  all  |strong="3605" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.6" \w* \w  night  |strong="3915" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.7" \w* \w  their anger  |strong="644" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.9" \w* \w  smolders ;  |strong="3463" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.8" \w* \f + \fr 7.6 \ft Literally "their baker sleeps" \f* \w  in the morning  |strong="1242" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.10" \w* \w  it  |strong="1931" srcloc="WLC:HOS.7.6.11" \w* \w  blazes  |